"title": "5327: governors",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5327: governors",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Those who ruled with an authority delegated to them by a higher ruler to whom they were responsible.</p>\n<h2>Joseph as governor of Egypt</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:6\">GEN 42:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:41\">GEN 41:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:43\">GEN 41:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:55\">GEN 41:55</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:8\">GEN 45:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:26\">GEN 45:26</a></p>\n<h2>Governors of Judah</h2>\n<h3>Gedaliah had a short period in office</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:22-2Kgs25:23\">2KI 25:22–25:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer40:7\">JER 40:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer40:11\">JER 40:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer41:2\">JER 41:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer41:18\">JER 41:18</a></p>\n<h3>Sheshbazzar laid the temple foundations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra5:14\">EZR 5:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra1:8\">EZR 1:8</a></p>\n<h3>Zerubbabel</h3>\n<p>Zerubbabel is possibly the same person as Sheshbazzar:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:1\">HAG 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:14\">HAG 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:2\">HAG 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:21\">HAG 2:21</a></p>\n<h3>Nehemiah rebuilt the walls of Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:14\">NEH 5:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:9\">NEH 8:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:1\">NEH 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:26\">NEH 12:26</a></p>\n<h3>Governors before Nehemiah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:15\">NEH 5:15</a></p>\n<h2>Persian governors</h2>\n<h3>Tattenai</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra5:3\">EZR 5:3</a></strong> <em>“Trans-Euphrates” (literally “beyond the river”, i.e., the Euphrates River) to the Persians included the areas of Aram, Phoenicia and Palestine.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra5:6\">EZR 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:6\">EZR 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:13\">EZR 6:13</a></p>\n<h3>Other governors of Trans-Euphrates</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:36\">EZR 8:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:7\">NEH 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:9\">NEH 2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:7\">NEH 3:7</a></p>\n<h3>Other Persian governors</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:12\">EST 3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:9\">EST 8:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:3\">EST 9:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:2-Dan3:3\">DAN 3:2–3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:27\">DAN 3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:7\">DAN 6:7</a></p>\n<h3>Satraps</h3>\n<p>Satraps were Persian provincial governors:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:36\">EZR 8:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:12\">EST 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:9\">EST 8:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:3\">EST 9:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:2-Dan3:3\">DAN 3:2–3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:27\">DAN 3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:1-Dan6:4\">DAN 6:1–6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:6\">DAN 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:7\">DAN 6:7</a></p>\n<h2>Other OT references to governors</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:30\">JDG 9:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:7\">1KI 4:7</a> <em>Solomon's twelve district governors</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:19\">1KI 4:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:5\">2KI 10:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:8\">2KI 23:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:14\">2CH 9:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:23\">JER 51:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:28\">JER 51:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:57\">JER 51:57</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:6\">EZK 23:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:12\">EZK 23:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:23\">EZK 23:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:8\">MAL 1:8</a></p>\n<h2>Roman governors</h2>\n<h3>Quirinius, governor of Syria</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:1-Luke2:2\">LUK 2:1–2:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Pilate, governor of Judea</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:2\">MAT 27:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:11\">MAT 27:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:14\">MAT 27:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:15\">MAT 27:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:21\">MAT 27:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:27\">MAT 27:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:14\">MAT 28:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:1\">LUK 3:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:20\">LUK 20:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:28\">JHN 18:28</a></p>\n<h3>Felix, governor of Judea</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:24\">ACT 23:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:26\">ACT 23:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:33-Acts23:34\">ACT 23:33–23:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:1\">ACT 24:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:10\">ACT 24:10</a></p>\n<h3>Festus, governor of Judea</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:30-Acts26:32\">ACT 26:30–26:32</a> <em>Festus did not understand Paul but might well have released him but for his (Paul's) appeal to Rome.</em></p>\n<h2>The governor of Damascus</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:32\">2CO 11:32</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Other NT references to governors</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:18\">MAT 10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:9\">MRK 13:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:12\">LUK 21:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:14\">1PE 2:14</a></p>\n<h2>Standards of performance of governors</h2>\n<h3>Some were good</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:39-Gen41:40\">GEN 41:39–41:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:27\">1KI 4:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:1\">2KI 10:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra5:16\">EZR 5:16</a></p>\n<h3>Some were bad</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:14-Neh5:15\">NEH 5:14–5:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:26\">ACT 24:26</a></p>",
